                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d183">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5131/1282a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Straus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-25T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 25, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>437. Garreau-Dombasle has been strongly stressing the importance of concluding
                    trade agreement negotiations before the expiry on November 15th of the French
                    Government’s power to sign an agreement. In view of French regional export
                    interests concerned, do you consider that prospects of serious new difficulties
                    are to be expected if an agreement is not signed by that date?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
